{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17567519","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17567519"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T00:03:03+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T00:03:03+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"19096"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"19096","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/19096"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.04,0.09,0.51,0.19,0.18]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11830"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"86442"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11830","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11830"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"19096"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"70722"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"26"},{"type":"tags","id":"28"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1497"},{"type":"tags","id":"1595"},{"type":"tags","id":"4979"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"11639"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27784"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43720"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44723"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"86442","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/86442"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 92-year-old woman has died on the medical ward. You are the intern asked to certify the death. The death was expected and occurred 30 minutes ago.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is NOT a required component of death certification examination?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Assessment of pupillary response to light","Observation for respiratory effort for 5 minutes","Testing corneal reflexes","Assessment of motor response to painful stimulus","Auscultation of heart sounds for 5 minutes"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EDeath certification is a formal process requiring documentation of specific clinical signs to confirm death. The examination must be thorough and systematic, with findings documented in the medical record.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETesting corneal reflexes\u003C/strong\u003E is NOT a required component of death certification. While it is sometimes performed in brain death testing, it is not part of the routine examination for death certification.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe following are all components of the death certification process:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAuscultation of heart sounds\u003C/strong\u003E for a minimum of five minutes is essential to confirm the absence of cardiac activity. This should be performed with the stethoscope in multiple positions over the precordium.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAssessment of pupillary response to light\u003C/strong\u003E is a required component. Fixed and dilated pupils that do not react to bright light are consistent with death.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EObservation for respiratory effort\u003C/strong\u003E for five minutes is mandatory. This includes visual inspection of the chest and abdomen for movement, and auscultation of breath sounds.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAssessment of motor response to painful stimulus\u003C/strong\u003E is required to confirm the absence of any response to central pain. This is typically performed by applying pressure to the supraorbital ridge or sternum.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAfter confirming death, the medical officer must complete the death certificate, including the cause of death and any contributing conditions. The examination findings should be documented in the medical record with the time and date of death certification.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Death certification requires confirmation of death through examination of specific clinical signs.","Documentation of the absence of heart sounds, breath sounds, pupillary reflexes, and motor response for five minutes is required as part of the formal death certification process.","Testing corneal reflexes is not part of routine death certification examination."],"references":["Verification of Death. In: NSW Health [online]. Accessed 2025 Feb. Available at: https://www.health.nsw.gov.au/patients/acp/Documents/verification-death.pdf"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"70722"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"19096"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"70722","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/70722"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-02-21T14:59:37+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-02-21T15:01:34+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11830"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"86442"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"26","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/26"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udd7c","name":"Critical Care Medicine","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"5"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"28","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/28"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc95","name":"Palliative Care","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":nul